      "contents": "Require Import Basics.Overture.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n(** * Building blocks for a globally nameless style of tactic reasoning *)\n\n(** ** [hyp] returns any hypothesis, with subsequent failures backtracking through all hypotheses *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Ltac hyp := multimatch goal with H : _ |- _ => constr:(H) end.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** [enforce foo] ensures that [foo] is well-typed *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Tactic Notation \"enforce\" open_constr(term) := idtac.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** [syntax_enforce [ H := body ]] ensures that [H] has a body which is syntactically equal to [body] *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Tactic Notation \"syntax_enforce\" \"[\" constr(H) \":=\" open_constr(body) \"]\" := let H' := (eval unfold H in H) in constr_eq H' body.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** [enforce [ x = y ]] ensures that two terms, possibly containing holes, are judgmentally equal *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Tactic Notation \"enforce\" \"[\" open_constr(x) \"=\" open_constr(y) \"]\" := unify x y.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** An example *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Goal Empty -> let X0 := tt in Empty -> Unit.",
